<font face="Times New Roman, Times, serif" size="4">Nativo L&oacute;pez on what's next in the struggle:</font><br>
<font face="Times New Roman, Times, serif" size="5"><b>"You get what you're ready to fight for"</b></font><p>
<font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2">May 5, 2006 | Page 5</font><p>

<font face="Times New Roman, Times, serif" size="3">NATIVO L&Oacute;PEZ is president of the Mexican American Political Association and a spokesperson for the Great American Boycott 2006--a national day of action for immigrant rights on May 1. In the lead-up to May 1, Nativo talked to SARAH KNOPP, a teacher in Los Angeles and Green Party candidate for state superintendent of schools in California, about the huge protests against anti-immigrant legislation and the future of the struggle.<p>
<p><font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="1">- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -</font></p>


<table width="264" align="right" border="0"><tr><td>
<img src="../../OtherImages/Soc06Speaker1.gif" width="252" height="18" border="0" align="right">
<table width="252" align="right" cellpadding="12" cellspacing="0" bgcolor="#FFCC66" border="0"><tr><td>
